Definition.WordDefinition: Acetal \Ac"e*tal\, n. [Acetic + alcohol.] (Chem.) A limpid, colorless, inflammable liquid from the slow oxidation of alcohol under the influence of platinum black. [1913 Webster]
acetal n : any organic compound formed by adding alcohol molecules to aldehyde molecules
